Description: Round-topped limestone stela with incised detail divided into three registers: 1 - Winged sun-disc with uraei. 2 - Six column of Hieroglyphic text including the cartouches of Sekhemraneferkhau Wepwawetemsaf. 3 - Scene of a figure and Wepwawet with a column of Hieroglyphic text inbetween.
Curator's comments: Published: HTBM 4: Plate 25 Bourriau, Pharaohs and Mortals, no. 58
Bibliographic references: Shaw & Nicholson 1995 / British Museum Dictionary of Ancient Egypt (p304)
